In version -05, section 5.2.4, I read:

> The DNS is centralized, and this brings up political and social
> concerns over control.

This is not a correct assessment. If the DNS were really centralized,
each time I want to add/modify something in bortzmeyer.org, I would
have to ask to the Center. (This was true of the previous system,
HOSTS.TXT, described in RFC 608.)

I suggest instead:

> The DNS is organized as a rooted tree, and this brings up political
> and social concerns over control.


