The current text says (section 5.2.4.2) that DPI is used to modify
DNS answers in Turkey. There is no evidence of that (specially in the
mentioned article), quite the contrary: during recent censorship
events in Turkey, switching to an alternative resolver worked, proving
there was no DPI (another trick used was route hijacking, see
presentation at RIPE
<https://ripe68.ripe.net/presentations/158-bortzmeyer-google-dns-turkey.pdf>)

I suggest to rewrite as
<https://github.com/bortzmeyer/IRTF-HRPC/commit/1edbf4e803841dd63340bcc8b6cf0d46d9bf3428>:

> all DNS protocol messages are inspected by the network, and
> objectionable content is distorted, as in China. [China replacing Turkey]

See
<https://mailarchive.ietf.org/arch/msg/hrpc/rBvp0nBo3EfVT-gaMJiKLU3TkEg> and
<https://mailarchive.ietf.org/arch/msg/hrpc/4B6TdRYBtdgRo_2euBsDf8ck5tI> for
previous remarks about Turkey.


