> 
> This might be a language issue. What is meant is that there is no IETF
> definition for what an 'open standard' is.

This gap is not quite an accident, though, and I think that may be
part of the reason you're hearing some anxiety about the target
audience for this document.  

And given that this is an RG inside the IRTF, I don't understand why
an IETF consensus about what an open standard is would matter anyway.

